Keywords: 



Patches applied:

 * falk@cs.fau.de--2008-common-intern/HscdSupport--mainline--0.8--patch-70
   
 * Merge from HscdSupport--devel--0.8
 - Added test_typename

 * falk@cs.fau.de--2008-common-intern/HscdSupport--mainline--0.8--patch-71
   
 * Merge from HscdSupport--devel--0.8
 * Change ListFacade to explicitly provide the types reference, const_reference, pointer and const_pointer.
 * No longer use CoSupport::Type::Const/Mutable to change between iterator and const_iterator now use
 - Type::STLIteratorSelector<C>::type to access const_iterator if container C is const and iterator otherwise.
 - Type::STLReverseIteratorSelector<C>::type to access const_reverse_iterator if container C is const and reverse_iterator otherwise.
 - Type::STLPointerSelector<C>::type to access const_pointer if container C is const and pointer otherwise.
 - Type::STLReferenceSelector<C>::type to access const_reference if container C is const and reference otherwise.

 * falk@cs.fau.de--2008-common-intern/HscdSupport--mainline--0.8--patch-72
   
 * Merge from HscdSupport--devel--0.8
 - Added FacadeTraits<const T>
   where FacadeTraits<const T>::Ref == FacadeTraits<T>::ConstRef
   and   FacadeTraits<const T>::Ptr == FacadeTraits<T>::ConstPtr, i.e.,
   If the facade object is const we can only get pointers to const
   objects even if we request a normal pointer.

 * falk@cs.fau.de--2008-common-intern/HscdSupport--mainline--0.8--patch-75
   
 * Merge from HscdSupport--devel--0.8
 - Concentrate face type definitions in FacadeTraits class.
 - Switched to boost::add_const and boost::remove_const from boost/type_traits for Facade.hpp
   Instead of Const<T::Ptr> use FacadeTraits<typename boost::add_const<T>::type>::Ptr
   Instead of Mutable<T::Ptr> use FacadeTraits<typename boost::remove_const<T>::type>::Ptr
 - Provide boost::add_reference/remove_reference boost::add_pointer/remove_pointer for Facade.hpp

